from\": 560, \"to\": 569}, {\"ngram\": \"the 48 gold medallists\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 597}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 606}, {\"ngram\": \"a 128-year tradition\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although the concept of purely amateur competition has long since disappeared from the modern Olympics with athletes often receiving payments from sponsors and professionals taking part for years, the World Athletics (WA) decision is a major shift.\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 923, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the concept\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"purely amateur competition\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 725}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympics\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 777}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 791}, {\"ngram\": \"payments\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 816}, {\"ngram\": \"sponsors\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 830}, {\"ngram\": \"professionals\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 848}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 860}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"WA\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"a major shift\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WA President Sebastian Coe said there had been no discussion with the International Olympic Committee, only that his organisation had given the IOC a heads-up shortly before announcing the $2.4 million prize pot.\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 938, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}, {\"begin\": 995, \"end\": 1026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1069, \"end\": 1072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.748122258905716e-36, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no discussion\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 985}, {\"ngram\": \"his organisation\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"a heads\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1080}, {\"ngram\": \"the $2.4 million prize pot\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1136}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"While it is impossible to put a marketable value on winning an Olympic medal, or on the commitment and focus it takes to even represent your country at an Olympic Games, it is important we make sure some of the revenues generated by our athletes are directly returned to those who make the Games the global spectacle that it is,\\\" Coe told reporters.\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a marketable value\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1188}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1216}, {\"ngram\": \"the commitment\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"your country\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1288}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"the revenues\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1359}, {\"ngram\": \"our athletes\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1435}, {\"ngram\": \"Coe\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1473}, {\"ngram\": \"reporters\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1488}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not believe this is remotely at variance with the concept that the IOC often talks about, which is recognising the efforts that our competitors make for the overall success of the Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.748122258905716e-36, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"variance\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1537}, {\"ngram\": \"the concept\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1554}, {\"ngram\": \"the efforts\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"our competitors\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1640}, {\"ngram\": \"the overall success\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1669}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1682}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Norway's Olympic 400m hurdles champion Karsten Warholm welcomed the news.\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1686, \"end\": 1692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.9999525439226389, \"rank\": 4.1142588724454305e-05, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 1725, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karsten Warholm\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karsten_Warholm\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the news\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 1758}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it's good so I want to salute them for it,\\\" he told Reuters.\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1822, \"end\": 1829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.534754099965906e-13, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It does not change my motivation to win because for the Olympics I am not in it for the money.\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my motivation\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1864}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1896}, {\"ngram\": \"the money\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gold medal is worth a lot more to me personally.\\\"\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The gold medal\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC said it was up to each International Federation (IF) and National Olympic Committee (NOC) to determine how to best serve their athletes and the development of their sports.\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 2162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1986, \"end\": 1989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.748122258905716e-36, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2047, \"end\": 2079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Olympic Committee (NOC)\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2047, \"end\": 2079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Olympic Committee (NOC)\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"each International Federation\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2037}, {\"ngram\": \"their athletes\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2125}, {\"ngram\": \"the development\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2145}, {\"ngram\": \"their sports\", \"from\": 2149, \"to\": 2161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The IOC redistributes 90% of all its income, in particular to the NOCs and IFs.\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2169, \"end\": 2172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.748122258905716e-36, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"90%\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2190}, {\"ngram\": \"all its income\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"the NOCs\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2235}, {\"ngram\": \"IFs\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2243}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This means that, every day, the equivalent of $4.2 million goes to help athletes and sports organisations at all levels around the world,\\\" the ruling body said.\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2405, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the equivalent\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2287}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2325}, {\"ngram\": \"sports organisations\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2350}, {\"ngram\": \"all levels\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2364}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"the ruling body\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A total of $540 million was allocated to the 28 sports at the Tokyo Games with World Athletics receiving the most at $40 million.\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2536, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2486, \"end\": 2501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.447235060579195e-16, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A total\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2414}, {\"ngram\": \"the 28 sports\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2461}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 2465, \"to\": 2480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AMATEUR ETHOS The amateur ethos of the Olympics, severely undermined for decades by the success of state-sponsored competitors from the former Eastern Bloc, was swept away when the IOC agreed to allow professional athletes to compete in tennis, soccer and ice hockey at the 1988 Seoul Games.\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2720, \"end\": 2723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.748122258905716e-36, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"AMATEUR\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2545}, {\"ngram\": \"The amateur ethos\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2569}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2585}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2618}, {\"ngram\": \"the success\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2633}, {\"ngram\": \"state-sponsored competitors\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2664}, {\"ngram\": \"the former Eastern Bloc\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2693}, {\"ngram\": \"professional athletes\", \"from\": 2739, \"to\": 2760}, {\"ngram\": \"tennis\", \"from\": 2775, \"to\": 2781}, {\"ngram\": \"soccer\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 2789}, {\"ngram\": \"ice hockey\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 2804}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1988 Seoul Games\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2828}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Basketball followed in 1992 and superstar professionals from the NBA gained huge attention when coming together in the United States \\\"Dream Team\\\", with most other sports subsequently removing restrictions on professionals taking part.\", \"from\": 2832, \"to\": 3066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2897, \"end\": 2900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999993625453711, \"rank\": 6.374024012858695e-07, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 2951, \"end\": 2964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9892630695049902, \"rank\": 0.010849661756539994, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Basketball\", \"from\": 2832, \"to\": 2842}, {\"ngram\": \"superstar professionals\", \"from\": 2864, \"to\": 2887}, {\"ngram\": \"huge attention\", \"from\": 2908, \"to\": 2922}, {\"ngram\": \"most other sports\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 3001}, {\"ngram\": \"restrictions\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3036}, {\"ngram\": \"professionals\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3053}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletics is the Olympics\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 biggest sport by number of participants and TV audiences but the vast majority of athletes, including many medallists, face a constant struggle for funding.\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3253, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletics\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3077}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 biggest sport\", \"from\": 3081, \"to\": 3110}, {\"ngram\": \"number\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3120}, {\"ngram\": \"participants\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3136}, {\"ngram\": \"TV audiences\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3153}, {\"ngram\": \"the vast majority\", \"from\": 3158, \"to\": 3175}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 3179, \"to\": 3187}, {\"ngram\": \"many medallists\", \"from\": 3199, \"to\": 3214}, {\"ngram\": \"a constant struggle\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3240}, {\"ngram\": \"funding\", \"from\": 3245, \"to\": 3252}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic silver and bronze medallists in athletics will also receive prize money, but only from the 2028 Los Angeles Games.\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3377, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic silver and bronze medallists\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3291}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3304}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 3323, \"to\": 3334}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Los Angeles Games\", \"from\": 3350, \"to\": 3376}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coe, who won 1,500 metres gold medals at the 1980 and 1984 Games, rejected the idea the new plan would undermine any amateur ethic.\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3510, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Coe\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3382}, {\"ngram\": \"1,500 metres\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3404}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3416}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1980 and 1984 Games\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3443}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 3454, \"to\": 3462}, {\"ngram\": \"the new plan\", \"from\": 3463, \"to\": 3475}, {\"ngram\": \"any amateur ethic\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3509}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am probably the last generation to have been on the 75p meal voucher and a second class rail ticket when competing for my own country,\\\" the 67-year-old Briton said.\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3679, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last generation\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3546}, {\"ngram\": \"the 75p meal\", \"from\": 3563, \"to\": 3575}, {\"ngram\": \"a second class rail ticket\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3614}, {\"ngram\": \"my own country\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3648}, {\"ngram\": \"the 67-year-old Briton\", \"from\": 3651, \"to\": 3673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So, I do understand the nature of the transition we have been in.\", \"from\": 3681, \"to\": 3747, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the nature\", \"from\": 3702, \"to\": 3712}, {\"ngram\": \"the transition\", \"from\": 3716, \"to\": 3730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a completely different planet from when I was competing,\\\" Coe added.\", \"from\": 3748, \"to\": 3822, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a completely different planet\", \"from\": 3754, \"to\": 3783}, {\"ngram\": \"Coe\", \"from\": 3812, \"to\": 3815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I want young athletes to look at our sport and think that this is financially viable for them.\", \"from\": 3824, \"to\": 3919, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"young athletes\", \"from\": 3832, \"to\": 3846}, {\"ngram\": \"our sport\", \"from\": 3858, \"to\": 3867}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For many, and for too long, it has not been and that's what I am now addressing.\\\"\", \"from\": 3920, \"to\": 4001, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS Athletics Olympics COE E-paper Newsletters Podcasts RSS Feed About Us Terms & Conditions Personal Data Protection Notice Need help?\", \"from\": 4002, \"to\": 4152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4002, \"end\": 4009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 4069, \"end\": 4077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wi